    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe `vim.str_byteindex` function with its new signature returns incorrect results for UTF-8–encoded strings when dealing with characters whose code points are above `U+0080` (for example, Cyrillic).\n```lua\nlocal word_ru = \"Слово\"\nlocal word_en = \"Words\"\nvim.notify(\"old_signature_ru \".. tostring(vim.str_byteindex(word_ru, 5, true)))\nvim.notify(\"old_signature_en \".. tostring(vim.str_byteindex(word_en, 5, true)))\nvim.notify(\"new_signature_ru \".. tostring(vim.str_byteindex(word_ru, \"utf-8\", 5, true))) \nvim.notify(\"new_signature_en \".. tostring(vim.str_byteindex(word_en, \"utf-8\", 5, true)))\n```\nOutput\n```\nold_signature_ru: 10\nold_signature_en: 5\nnew_signature_ru: 5 --incorrect\nnew_signature_en: 5\n```\n### Error in the source code.\nError in `neovim/runtime/lua/vim/_editor.lua` at lines 725–730.\n```lua\nif encoding == 'utf-8' then\n    if index > len then\n      return strict_indexing and error('index out of range') or len\n    end\n    return index\n  end\n```\nThe assertion that byteindex equals index holds true only for Unicode characters with code points `U+0000`–`U+007F`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Run in nvim: `vim.str_byteindex(\"слово\", \"utf-8\", 5, true)`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n1. Output: `10`\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian GNU/Linux 12 (bookworm)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.41.1-2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nInstall from download",
