            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This is intended behavior. UTF-8 is the _native_ encoding of unicode strings, and thus these functions are idempotent when used with the `\"utf-8\"` encoding. if you want to convert codepoint indices to byte indices, use `\"utf-32\"` instead (as the UTF-32 unit is codepoints).\n\nLeaving this open as this special case is probably worth pointing out in the docs. ",
